1
00:00:11,958 --> 00:00:14,083
Oh.
It's you, Miyako.

2
00:00:14,166 --> 00:00:16,083
Whoa, I hardly recognized you!

3
00:00:16,166 --> 00:00:18,125
-Are you okay?
-Yeah, I'm fine.

4
00:00:18,208 --> 00:00:21,041
I just haven't slept
in a couple of days.

5
00:00:21,125 --> 00:00:23,125
Anyway, you came
at the perfect time.

6
00:00:23,208 --> 00:00:24,208
What?

7
00:00:24,291 --> 00:00:25,708
[ITSUKI]
Could you do me a solid

8
00:00:25,791 --> 00:00:27,833
and deliver this to my editor?

9
00:00:29,041 --> 00:00:30,791
Thanks, you're the best.

10
00:00:30,875 --> 00:00:33,000
-[thud]
-Itsuki?

11
00:00:33,083 --> 00:00:35,166
Like hell you're fine,
you look terrible!

12
00:00:35,250 --> 00:00:36,583
[snoring]

13
00:00:38,250 --> 00:00:39,250
Man.

14
00:00:39,333 --> 00:00:41,500
What am I going to do with you?

15
00:02:21,250 --> 00:02:23,458
Do I just use this
to call him down?

16
00:02:23,541 --> 00:02:24,875
Oh.

17
00:02:26,083 --> 00:02:27,458
May I help you, miss?

18
00:02:27,541 --> 00:02:30,041
Uh, yeah.
I was told to--

19
00:02:30,125 --> 00:02:32,375
Uh, Itsuki Hashima asked me

20
00:02:32,458 --> 00:02:34,583
to deliver something
to Mr. Toki for him.

21
00:02:34,666 --> 00:02:37,291
Okay. Then why don't you
come in.

22
00:02:41,375 --> 00:02:42,541
[YAMAGATA]
Delivery!

23
00:02:42,625 --> 00:02:43,958
Hey, Ken-Ken!

24
00:02:44,041 --> 00:02:46,000
You shut your mouth,
you little-sister obsessed

25
00:02:46,083 --> 00:02:47,416
freak o' nature!

26
00:02:48,791 --> 00:02:50,041
[snoring]

27
00:02:50,125 --> 00:02:52,250
Is everything okay with him?

28
00:02:52,333 --> 00:02:54,041
Happens all the time.

29
00:02:54,125 --> 00:02:55,708
That messy one's his desk,

30
00:02:55,791 --> 00:02:57,833
so why don't you just
leave it there for him?

31
00:02:57,916 --> 00:02:59,208
All right.

32
00:02:59,291 --> 00:03:00,208
[sighs]

33
00:03:00,291 --> 00:03:01,750
[continues snoring]

34
00:03:06,208 --> 00:03:08,625
He must be pushing himself
extra hard.

35
00:03:08,708 --> 00:03:11,458
It's always like this
when proofreading day is near.

36
00:03:11,541 --> 00:03:13,583
Really? Hmm.

37
00:03:13,666 --> 00:03:15,875
Hey.
Isn't that...?

38
00:03:15,958 --> 00:03:18,708
It's the cover for
Nayuta Kani's new volume.

39
00:03:18,791 --> 00:03:20,708
Supposed to go
on sale this month,

40
00:03:20,791 --> 00:03:22,958
but the manuscript
hasn't been turned in yet.

41
00:03:23,041 --> 00:03:24,750
[MIYAKO]
Well, that's no good.

42
00:03:24,833 --> 00:03:26,833
You can say that again.

43
00:03:26,916 --> 00:03:29,291
And I haven't been able
to get a hold of her.

44
00:03:29,375 --> 00:03:30,375
[sighs]

45
00:03:30,458 --> 00:03:32,458
[MIYAKO]
Um...

46
00:03:32,541 --> 00:03:35,250
If you'd like,
I could check up on her.

47
00:03:35,333 --> 00:03:36,291
[YAMAGATA]
What?

48
00:03:40,333 --> 00:03:42,208
Yeah, I can go see her now.

49
00:03:43,291 --> 00:03:44,208
Sorry.

50
00:03:44,291 --> 00:03:45,750
But who are you?

51
00:03:47,375 --> 00:03:48,666
Come on in, Myaa!

52
00:03:48,750 --> 00:03:50,750
Now don't be shy,
take off your clothes!

53
00:03:50,833 --> 00:03:52,416
[MIYAKO]
Uh... 'Kay?

54
00:03:53,708 --> 00:03:55,625
Hold on, I am not here
to mess around, girl!

55
00:03:55,708 --> 00:03:58,000
Aw, that's a shame.

56
00:03:58,083 --> 00:04:00,791
Nayu, I heard you haven't
turned in your manuscript yet.

57
00:04:00,875 --> 00:04:02,000
[squeals]

58
00:04:02,083 --> 00:04:03,875
[MIYAKO]
I saw your editor and she said

59
00:04:03,958 --> 00:04:06,375
she'd been up all night
waiting for it.

60
00:04:06,458 --> 00:04:08,708
How much longer
do you think it'll take?

61
00:04:08,791 --> 00:04:09,916
Um, I dunno.

62
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:11,416
I'm almost done with the amount

63
00:04:11,500 --> 00:04:13,041
I'm supposed to write.

64
00:04:13,125 --> 00:04:14,333
But I just haven't been able

65
00:04:14,416 --> 00:04:16,416
to keep myself
in the zone lately.

66
00:04:16,500 --> 00:04:17,750
[MIYAKO]
In the zone?

67
00:04:17,833 --> 00:04:19,500
We should totally have some fun!

68
00:04:19,583 --> 00:04:21,166
I just know that I'll feel
more motivated

69
00:04:21,250 --> 00:04:23,125
to get my work done
if you play with me.

70
00:04:23,208 --> 00:04:24,166
No way.

71
00:04:24,250 --> 00:04:25,291
Aww.

72
00:04:25,375 --> 00:04:26,916
Hey. Don't be like that.

73
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:28,375
We can hang out and do
whatever you want

74
00:04:28,458 --> 00:04:30,000
when your work's done.

75
00:04:31,125 --> 00:04:33,666
I guess you leave me no choice.

76
00:04:35,500 --> 00:04:36,541
But I have one condition.

77
00:04:36,625 --> 00:04:39,125
Let me use your lap as a pillow!

78
00:04:39,208 --> 00:04:40,291
It'll recharge my batteries!

79
00:04:40,375 --> 00:04:43,208
You're like my power cable.

80
00:04:43,291 --> 00:04:45,000
I don't even know
what that means.

81
00:04:45,083 --> 00:04:46,666
But if you really think
it'll help

82
00:04:46,750 --> 00:04:48,500
then I can deal with it.

83
00:04:48,583 --> 00:04:49,875
C'mon.

84
00:04:49,958 --> 00:04:51,875
[laughs]

85
00:04:51,958 --> 00:04:53,625
Wait, you write it
on your phone?

86
00:04:53,708 --> 00:04:54,958
Yeah, sometimes.

87
00:04:55,041 --> 00:04:57,208
I just use whatever I feel
like at the time.

88
00:04:57,291 --> 00:05:00,416
I'll use my laptop,
a stand-alone word processor,

89
00:05:00,500 --> 00:05:01,958
or even paper and pencil.

90
00:05:02,041 --> 00:05:03,458
Well that's convenient.

91
00:05:05,541 --> 00:05:06,708
If you have to be naked,

92
00:05:06,791 --> 00:05:08,250
I guess you're stuck
in this room

93
00:05:08,333 --> 00:05:09,416
no matter what you use.

94
00:05:09,500 --> 00:05:10,916
Yeah.

95
00:05:11,000 --> 00:05:13,166
But laying on your lap
is a good way to mix it up!

96
00:05:13,250 --> 00:05:15,083
[MIYAKO]
You got me there.

97
00:05:15,166 --> 00:05:16,500
Okay, enough messin' around.

98
00:05:16,583 --> 00:05:18,125
Time to get to work!

99
00:05:18,208 --> 00:05:19,791
[phone whirring]

100
00:05:20,958 --> 00:05:22,500
Wow. You're fast.

101
00:05:26,625 --> 00:05:28,625
Manuscript done and submitted!

102
00:05:28,708 --> 00:05:30,291
Good job.
I'm proud of you, Nayu.

103
00:05:30,375 --> 00:05:31,250
[laughs]

104
00:05:31,333 --> 00:05:33,000
Thanks to you, Myaa.

105
00:05:33,083 --> 00:05:34,708
You should be my editor
from now on.

106
00:05:34,791 --> 00:05:36,916
You're great with motivation.

107
00:05:37,000 --> 00:05:39,583
Why are things not going well
with your real editor?

108
00:05:39,666 --> 00:05:41,083
No, things are fine with her.

109
00:05:41,166 --> 00:05:43,000
Then you should probably
keep her in the loop

110
00:05:43,083 --> 00:05:44,500
on your work.

111
00:05:44,583 --> 00:05:45,958
It's not like talking to her

112
00:05:46,041 --> 00:05:49,000
makes me finish
my manuscripts any faster.

113
00:05:49,083 --> 00:05:51,041
Hey, you don't know
that for sure.

114
00:05:51,125 --> 00:05:53,333
Maybe if you actually discussed
your story with her,

115
00:05:53,416 --> 00:05:55,500
she'd give you
some good ideas.

116
00:05:55,583 --> 00:05:56,583
Hmm.

117
00:05:57,750 --> 00:05:58,625
[giggles]

118
00:05:58,708 --> 00:06:00,083
Nah, that wouldn't happen.

119
00:06:01,666 --> 00:06:02,458
[sighs]

120
00:06:02,541 --> 00:06:04,541
Okay.

121
00:06:04,625 --> 00:06:08,458
Ah. What about the fifth line
on page twenty-one?

122
00:06:08,541 --> 00:06:10,083
[YAMAGATA]
Seriously, you're a lifesaver.

123
00:06:10,166 --> 00:06:11,666
Thank you so much.

124
00:06:11,750 --> 00:06:13,375
Oh, I didn't do
anything special.

125
00:06:13,458 --> 00:06:16,125
But we can release
the book thanks to you.

126
00:06:16,208 --> 00:06:18,666
-[sighs]
-Wait, what's wrong?

127
00:06:18,750 --> 00:06:21,208
Now I have to go apologize
to the printers,

128
00:06:21,291 --> 00:06:23,958
the proofreaders,
and the marketing department.

129
00:06:24,041 --> 00:06:27,125
Not the person who couldn't
make the deadline, but me.

130
00:06:27,208 --> 00:06:29,708
I always get stuck
with this stuff.

131
00:06:29,791 --> 00:06:30,708
[exasperated sigh]

132
00:06:30,791 --> 00:06:32,750
I'm well aware that it's my job.

133
00:06:32,833 --> 00:06:34,250
It's what I do.

134
00:06:34,333 --> 00:06:36,250
I just hate getting
the runaround from a little girl

135
00:06:36,333 --> 00:06:38,416
who just happens to be
our most valuable author.

136
00:06:38,500 --> 00:06:40,875
So, um...
I'm guessing that you two

137
00:06:40,958 --> 00:06:43,333
aren't exactly getting along
at the moment?

138
00:06:43,416 --> 00:06:45,166
-We get along.
-[TOKI talking on phone]

139
00:06:45,250 --> 00:06:46,666
But the two of us aren't
creating something together

140
00:06:46,750 --> 00:06:49,250
like those guys are.
Understand?

141
00:06:49,333 --> 00:06:51,375
Well, then maybe
you should talk more

142
00:06:51,458 --> 00:06:53,000
about the content
of her stories.

143
00:06:53,083 --> 00:06:54,583
-[YAMAGATA] No.
-[TOKI yelling]

144
00:06:54,666 --> 00:06:56,166
[YAMAGATA] There's virtually
nothing anyone

145
00:06:56,250 --> 00:06:59,333
could contribute
to better her works.

146
00:06:59,416 --> 00:07:01,041
Even though I'm her editor,

147
00:07:01,125 --> 00:07:03,208
I'm basically
just fixing her typos.

148
00:07:03,291 --> 00:07:06,000
It's infuriating, honestly.

149
00:07:06,083 --> 00:07:07,416
If it's so frustrating,

150
00:07:07,500 --> 00:07:09,500
why don't you
just quit being her editor?

151
00:07:09,583 --> 00:07:12,041
It's never crossed my mind
and it never will.

152
00:07:12,125 --> 00:07:13,833
Are you sure?

153
00:07:13,916 --> 00:07:15,166
Never?

154
00:07:15,250 --> 00:07:17,500
Yes, I'm sure,
and I'll tell you why.

155
00:07:17,583 --> 00:07:22,083
If I quit I wouldn't be the
first one to read her novels.

156
00:07:22,166 --> 00:07:24,041
Then you must love her work.

157
00:07:24,125 --> 00:07:25,916
That's nice to hear.

158
00:07:26,000 --> 00:07:27,833
[TOKI]
Wait. Yeah. Okay. Fine.

159
00:07:27,916 --> 00:07:30,250
I hate to admit it,
but you're right.

160
00:07:30,333 --> 00:07:31,416
[TOKI]
Okay. Aaah!

161
00:07:31,500 --> 00:07:34,250
Ah!
Damn it, shut up for a sec!

162
00:07:34,333 --> 00:07:36,166
We're getting nowhere
over the phone like this!

163
00:07:36,250 --> 00:07:37,958
I'm coming to your place
right now!

164
00:07:38,041 --> 00:07:39,375
Stupid kid.

165
00:07:39,458 --> 00:07:40,458
[TOKI growls]

166
00:07:42,291 --> 00:07:45,250
If I had to do what he does,
I'd be angry too.

167
00:07:51,583 --> 00:07:52,666
[HARUTO]
All right.

168
00:07:52,750 --> 00:07:54,000
In celebration
of our dear friends

169
00:07:54,083 --> 00:07:56,541
Itsuki and Nayu
releasing new volumes,

170
00:07:56,625 --> 00:07:58,250
we toast!

171
00:07:58,333 --> 00:08:00,000
[ALL]
Congratulations!

172
00:08:00,083 --> 00:08:02,583
I wouldn't be here
if it wasn't for you, Myaa!

173
00:08:02,666 --> 00:08:04,500
So thank you very much!

174
00:08:04,583 --> 00:08:06,000
Did Miyako help you out?

175
00:08:06,083 --> 00:08:07,583
Um?

176
00:08:09,416 --> 00:08:11,541
Yeah. She got na--

177
00:08:11,625 --> 00:08:13,875
I just hung out
and kept her company.

178
00:08:13,958 --> 00:08:15,416
Okay.

179
00:08:15,500 --> 00:08:16,875
You know, now that I think
about it,

180
00:08:16,958 --> 00:08:19,041
Kaiko thanked you
for helping her too.

181
00:08:19,125 --> 00:08:20,500
What did you do?

182
00:08:22,541 --> 00:08:23,750
It was nothing!

183
00:08:23,833 --> 00:08:25,666
Seriously, don't worry about it.

184
00:08:25,750 --> 00:08:28,000
Now let's drop it
and if you bring it up again,

185
00:08:28,083 --> 00:08:29,166
I'll break your collarbone.

186
00:08:29,250 --> 00:08:31,916
Why so specific?

187
00:08:32,000 --> 00:08:34,250
Now I'm even more curious
what she did.

188
00:08:35,708 --> 00:08:36,958
[ITSUKI sighs]

189
00:08:37,041 --> 00:08:38,916
It's nice to be able
to take my time eating

190
00:08:39,000 --> 00:08:40,791
now that
I'm done working.

191
00:08:40,875 --> 00:08:43,708
Yeah, I try not to eat too much
before a deadline, too.

192
00:08:43,791 --> 00:08:45,416
Don't wanna get tired
and fall asleep.

193
00:08:45,500 --> 00:08:46,583
[NAYUTA]
Same here.

194
00:08:46,666 --> 00:08:47,583
What do you mean?

195
00:08:47,666 --> 00:08:49,833
You never worry about deadlines.

196
00:08:49,916 --> 00:08:51,875
Well, sure I always
finish my work on time,

197
00:08:51,958 --> 00:08:53,416
but I get tired
when I eat too much.

198
00:08:53,500 --> 00:08:54,875
So I can imagine what it's like

199
00:08:54,958 --> 00:08:56,958
to do that the night
before a deadline.

200
00:08:57,041 --> 00:08:58,958
In other words,
you've never done that.

201
00:08:59,041 --> 00:09:01,791
[chuckles]

202
00:09:01,875 --> 00:09:03,208
[sighs]

203
00:09:03,291 --> 00:09:05,583
Okay. Now that
we're all relaxed,

204
00:09:05,666 --> 00:09:07,083
what do you say
we play a game?

205
00:09:07,166 --> 00:09:09,166
Yeah. Good idea.

206
00:09:09,250 --> 00:09:11,083
What did you have in mind?

207
00:09:11,166 --> 00:09:12,583
Huh...

208
00:09:13,750 --> 00:09:16,125
How about Once Upon a Time?

209
00:09:20,291 --> 00:09:21,666
[whistle blows]

210
00:09:21,750 --> 00:09:23,166
[HARUTO]
Once Upon a Time is a game

211
00:09:23,250 --> 00:09:25,000
in which all players
are storytellers,

212
00:09:25,083 --> 00:09:27,583
creating a story, together.

213
00:09:27,666 --> 00:09:29,541
Each player has an ending card
that has,

214
00:09:29,625 --> 00:09:32,000
you guessed it, the ending
to their story on it.

215
00:09:32,083 --> 00:09:33,791
They also have
a number of story cards

216
00:09:33,875 --> 00:09:35,625
that are used
to build their plot.

217
00:09:35,708 --> 00:09:37,666
The first player to use up
all of their story cards

218
00:09:37,750 --> 00:09:39,833
and complete the story
with their ending card

219
00:09:39,916 --> 00:09:41,416
is declared the winner.

220
00:09:41,500 --> 00:09:43,791
Now pay attention,
'cause this part's important.

221
00:09:43,875 --> 00:09:46,291
If any idea from one of
your story cards comes up

222
00:09:46,375 --> 00:09:47,875
while another storyteller
is speaking,

223
00:09:47,958 --> 00:09:49,291
you can present your card

224
00:09:49,375 --> 00:09:51,833
and steal the position
of storyteller from them.

225
00:09:51,916 --> 00:09:53,083
Oh, I get it.

226
00:09:53,166 --> 00:09:54,750
So you want it to be your turn,

227
00:09:54,833 --> 00:09:57,000
because that means you can take
the story in a direction

228
00:09:57,083 --> 00:09:59,083
that uses your cards
and ends with your conclusion.

229
00:09:59,166 --> 00:10:01,166
[HARUTO] There's also an
interrupt card that can be used

230
00:10:01,250 --> 00:10:03,375
when a similar type
of story card is presented

231
00:10:03,458 --> 00:10:06,250
letting a player immediately
steal the turn for themselves.

232
00:10:06,333 --> 00:10:07,666
So be prepared for that.

233
00:10:07,750 --> 00:10:09,500
[ALL]
All right. Okay.

234
00:10:09,583 --> 00:10:11,041
You ready?

235
00:10:11,125 --> 00:10:13,291
Let's decide who goes first
with rock-paper-scissors.

236
00:10:14,458 --> 00:10:15,833
Cool.

237
00:10:15,916 --> 00:10:17,833
Looks like I'll be treating you
to a new story

238
00:10:17,916 --> 00:10:19,291
free of charge.

239
00:10:19,375 --> 00:10:21,375
Once upon a time,
there was an older brother

240
00:10:21,458 --> 00:10:23,375
and his ever-faithful
younger sister.

241
00:10:23,458 --> 00:10:25,333
[HARUTO]
Of course you got that one.

242
00:10:25,416 --> 00:10:26,750
Are we sure we shuffled?

243
00:10:26,833 --> 00:10:28,333
This is divine intervention

244
00:10:28,416 --> 00:10:30,125
telling me to make
a sister story.

245
00:10:30,208 --> 00:10:32,416
I don't even need to say this,
since it's implied,

246
00:10:32,500 --> 00:10:35,041
but the little sister
is young and beautiful.

247
00:10:35,125 --> 00:10:36,500
Yes!

248
00:10:37,750 --> 00:10:39,708
That makes me the storyteller!

249
00:10:39,791 --> 00:10:43,000
I didn't expect the first player
to be interrupted so quickly.

250
00:10:43,083 --> 00:10:44,541
[ITSUKI groans]

251
00:10:44,625 --> 00:10:46,125
[HARUTO]
When the storyteller changes,

252
00:10:46,208 --> 00:10:47,875
the player who was interrupted
has to take

253
00:10:47,958 --> 00:10:50,208
a new story card from the pile.

254
00:10:50,291 --> 00:10:51,416
[ITSUKI groans]

255
00:10:51,500 --> 00:10:53,791
The little sister
was very beautiful.

256
00:10:53,875 --> 00:10:55,750
But unfortunately,
someone put a curse on her

257
00:10:55,833 --> 00:10:58,666
and she was turned into
a not-so-beautiful wolf.

258
00:10:58,750 --> 00:10:59,958
Huh?

259
00:11:00,041 --> 00:11:02,000
Why you gotta ruin
the sister like that?

260
00:11:02,083 --> 00:11:03,750
The one who turned
