00:20:28,083 --> 00:20:29,333
but there are more
important things

521
00:20:29,416 --> 00:20:31,041
than messing around
with a cute girl.

522
00:20:31,125 --> 00:20:32,333
Aren't there?

523
00:20:35,500 --> 00:20:37,333
But I'm curious.

524
00:20:37,416 --> 00:20:40,208
What exactly do you mean
by being equal to her?

525
00:20:40,291 --> 00:20:42,083
You wanna beat her in sales?

526
00:20:42,166 --> 00:20:45,000
or get some literary award
that she doesn't have yet?

527
00:20:45,083 --> 00:20:46,500
I dunno.

528
00:20:46,583 --> 00:20:48,583
But for now,
I'm gonna at least

529
00:20:48,666 --> 00:20:50,375
try to become
someone more significant

530
00:20:50,458 --> 00:20:52,708
if we ever decide
to get married.

531
00:20:52,791 --> 00:20:54,875
Getting an anime would be a good
first step towards that,

532
00:20:54,958 --> 00:20:56,166
you know?

533
00:20:56,250 --> 00:20:58,083
An anime's just the first step?

534
00:20:58,166 --> 00:21:00,333
Yeah, maybe to you.

535
00:21:00,416 --> 00:21:02,250
You aim high, man.

536
00:21:02,333 --> 00:21:04,541
But still.
You're right.

537
00:21:04,625 --> 00:21:06,875
Considering your
eventual goal here,

538
00:21:06,958 --> 00:21:09,000
an anime's just a checkpoint.

539
00:21:09,083 --> 00:21:10,541
[ITSUKI sighs]
Exactly.

540
00:21:11,833 --> 00:21:13,208
[HARUTO]
Man, this is good.

541
00:21:13,291 --> 00:21:14,375
[ITSUKI]
Yeah, dude,

542
00:21:14,458 --> 00:21:16,208
good call on
the beer and sausages.

543
00:21:16,291 --> 00:21:17,708
[HARUTO]
Speaking of which,

544
00:21:17,791 --> 00:21:19,916
I want to go to Germany,
or Belgium someday.

545
00:22:51,416 --> 00:22:54,333
This girl is
insanely talented.

546
00:22:54,416 --> 00:22:55,666
[phone buzzes]

547
00:22:58,708 --> 00:22:59,666
Yeah?

548
00:22:59,750 --> 00:23:00,833
[TOKI]
Itsuki.

549
00:23:00,916 --> 00:23:02,500
I have something
I have to tell you.

550
00:23:02,583 --> 00:23:03,875
What?

551
00:23:03,958 --> 00:23:05,833
Was there an emergency reprint
or something?

552
00:23:05,916 --> 00:23:07,333
[TOKI]
Oh, you knew about that?

553
00:23:07,416 --> 00:23:08,583
Wait.
Really?

554
00:23:08,666 --> 00:23:10,208
[TOKI]
Yeah, for Kani's new volume,

555
00:23:10,291 --> 00:23:11,833
not "Mahou Academy."

556
00:23:11,916 --> 00:23:13,375
Oh.

557
00:23:13,458 --> 00:23:15,666
The amount of copies you guys
printed for her new book

558
00:23:15,750 --> 00:23:17,000
is already higher

559
00:23:17,083 --> 00:23:19,083
than all of
"Mahou Academy"'s combined.

560
00:23:19,166 --> 00:23:21,666
[TOKI] And she's so popular,
even that wasn't enough.

561
00:23:21,750 --> 00:23:24,791
Did you just call me so you
could brag about her sales?

562
00:23:24,875 --> 00:23:26,333
[TOKI]
No, sorry.

563
00:23:26,416 --> 00:23:30,500
I should probably
congratulate you.

564
00:23:30,583 --> 00:23:33,916
"Mahou Academy" has been
greenlit for an anime.

565
00:23:35,333 --> 00:23:36,958
[ITSUKI shudders]

